Vice President Biden met with Secretary General Shigeru Ishiba of Japan at the White House to discuss the importance of the U.S.-Japan Alliance to regional and global security. They talked about Russia's violation of Ukraine's sovereignty and steps taken by both countries to impose costs on Russia. The Vice President emphasized the need to continue building strong support for the alliance, including the successful conclusion of Trans-Pacific Partnership negotiations. They also agreed to cooperate on the realignment of U.S. forces in Japan to reduce the impact of U.S. bases in Okinawa while enhancing the deterrent value of the Alliance.